## Error Analysis

**The error:** `Installed (but unpackaged) file(s) found` — rpmbuild detected files in BUILDROOT that aren't listed in the `%files` section.

**Missing files fall into 4 categories:**

| Category | Files | Solution |
|----------|-------|----------|
| **Binaries/scripts** | `/usr/bin/gawkbug`, profile.d scripts | Add to `%files` |
| **Plugins (.so)** | `/usr/lib/gawk/*.so` (12 shared objects) | Add to `%files` or split into `-devel` subpackage |
| **Man pages** | `/usr/share/man/man3/*.3am.gz` (10 files) | Add to `%files` |
| **Info images** | `/usr/share/info/*-figure*.png`, `gawk_statist.jpg` | Add to `%files` or `-devel` subpackage |
| **Headers** | `/usr/include/gawkapi.h` | Should go in `-devel` subpackage |
| **Debug symbols** | `/usr/lib/debug/...` | Handled by `find-debuginfo`; exclude from main package |

## Solution

Add all missing files to `%files`. The simplest approach that preserves full functionality:

```diff
--- a/gawk.spec
+++ b/gawk.spec
@@ ... @@
 %files
 %defattr(-,root,root)
 %doc AUTHORS COPYING NEWS POSIX.STD README README_d
+/usr/bin/gawkbug
 /bin/awk
 /bin/gawk
 /usr/bin/awk
 /usr/bin/gawk
+%dir %{_libdir}/gawk
+%{_libdir}/gawk/*.so
 /%dir %{_libdir}/awk
 %{_libdir}/awk/grcat
 %{_libdir}/awk/pwcat
 %dir /usr/share/awk
 /usr/share/awk/*.awk
+/etc/profile.d/gawk.csh
+/etc/profile.d/gawk.sh
 /usr/share/locale/*/LC_MESSAGES/*.mo
+%doc %{_infodir}/*.info.gz
+%{_infodir}/gawk_api-figure1.png
+%{_infodir}/gawk_api-figure2.png
+%{_infodir}/gawk_api-figure3.png
+%{_infodir}/gawk_array-elements.png
+%{_infodir}/gawk_general-program.png
+%{_infodir}/gawk_process-flow.png
+%{_infodir}/gawk_statist.jpg
+/usr/share/man/man3/*.3am.gz
 /%doc %{_mandir}/man1/*.1.gz
```

**To apply and rebuild:**
```bash
# Replace the entire %files section with the corrected version:
cat > /home/abuild/rpmbuild/SPECS/gawk.spec << 'SPECEOF'
... (full spec with fixed %files) ...
SPECEOF

# Then rebuild
